The tested device (DUT) is a PE-router running 6PE (IPv6 over BGP-LU with IPv4 next hops).
It runs OSPFv2 and LDP with a P-router over an IPv4-only core,
and has an IPv4 IBGP session with another PE-router. The hosts are attached
via IPv6-only links and communicate using IPv6 across the MPLS core.

The validation test checks end-to-end IPv6 connectivity between Linux hosts
attached to the PE-routers across a BGP-free MPLS core using 6PE .

